{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make Child Benefit rules for separated parents reflect active time with parents",
        "additional_details": "I want the Government to change who gets priority for Child Benefit, so that active time during the day is considered, and not just who a child lives with.\r\n \r\nI believe it is not fair that Child Benefit is given to the parent with whom a child primarily lives, without considering how much active time a child spends with each parent. Please change these rules to reflect the active time children spend with parents.\r\n",
        "background": "I have lost Child Benefit for my children because their primary home is with their father. This will have a massive impact on my finances.",
